                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d333">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/12214: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gunther</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-19T20:00:00+02:00"
                            >June 19, 1941—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 20—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>557. The French Air Attaché tells me that he has been informed by the Rumanian
                    General Staff that the Russians have 70 divisions in Bessarabia and that these
                    far outnumber the opposing German and Rumanian divisions in that region. He also
                    said that in Rumanian military circles it was generally expected that the German
                    attack on Russia would be launched on the morning of June 21 but that on account
                    of the extremely wet weather which has persisted for the last week and still
                    continues the attack might be adjourned 4 or 5 days.</p>
                <p>I might add that extensive plans have been prepared by the Rumanian authorities
                    for the evacuation of the Government and the foreign Diplomatic Corps in the
                    event of war.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gunther</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
